I am building "SpendBuddy AI", a mobile application that combines real-time group messaging with a shared expense management system (similar to Splitwise).

The Tech Stack: > * Backend: Go (Golang)

Database: PostgreSQL (Primary) + Redis (for Caching/WebSockets)

Auth: JWT-based, supporting Google OAuth2 and manual Email OTP verification.

Real-time: WebSockets for chat and instant balance updates.

The Architecture: > I want to follow Clean Architecture (Domain, Usecase, Repository, and Delivery layers). The project must be highly concurrent, memory-efficient, and use sqlc or pgx for type-safe, high-performance database interactions.